.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.MONTHSINYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.monthsInYear \-
Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.monthsInYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]monthsInYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a positive integer
representing the number of months in the year of this date.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
For the ISO 8601 calendar, this is always 12, but in other calendar
systems it may differ.
For example, in calendars using leap months, leap years will have one
more month than common years.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]monthsInYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using monthsInYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date2.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 12\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2023\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date3.monthsInYear); \f[I]// 13; 2023 is a Chinese leap year\f[R]
.EE
.SS Changing to the second last month of the year
You can use \f[CR]monthsInYear\f[R] to change to the second last month
of the year:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] secondLastMonth = date.with({ month: date.monthsInYear \- 1 });
console.log(secondLastMonth.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-11\-01\f[R]
.EE
